ts, its austere yet rich images, offers splinters of testimony and objection. It negotiates a constantly changing world, scavenging through scraps of experience, spaces around words, and remnants of emotion for a language that enfolds the enormity of what we cannot express.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aImmigrantsvPoetry. 0aKorean AmericansvPoetry. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  aamerican poetry.  acolonial.  acolonies.  acolonization.  aconfessional.  aconversation.  acreative writing.  adisease.  aenglish poetry.  afirst language.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  aimmigrant poetry.  aimmigration.  alanguage loss.  alife story.  aliterature.  aloaded silence.  alyric poetry.  alyric.  apeace.  apersonal.  apoetic.  apoetics.  apoetry collection.  apoetry.  atrue story.  awar.  awartime.  awriting poetry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023131340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092784140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520927841423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520927841/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY